  <h2>About this website</h2>
  <p>Although this website does not feature a true portfolio of my work as a Web Developer, I hope that <em>the website itself</em> will function as an example of my front-end coding skills. The entire site I designed and built from scratch. The only things on this site I did not personally create are <a href="https://jquery.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">jQuery</a> and the <a href="https://github.com/desandro/imagesloaded" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">imagesLoaded plugin</a> (used for the "loading" effect in the art &amp; photo galleries). The content is all static HTML, built using <a href="http://handlebarsjs.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Handlebars</a> and <a href="http://gruntjs.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Grunt</a>. The CSS was compiled from Sass, and borrows from <a href="http://meyerweb.com/eric/tools/css/reset/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Eric Meyer's CSS Reset</a>. The galleries were custom-built with my own JavaScript. The site is hosted with <a href="https://pages.github.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Github Pages</a>. The blog is hosted on Tumblr, using a custom, responsive Tumblr theme I built from scratch, and a customized version of <a href="http://fancybox.net/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Fancybox</a>. If you want to see more of how the site is built, feel free to <a href="https://github.com/charliethomason/portfolio-site" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">view the source code for this website</a>. If you're interested in how the art and photo galleries work, you can <a href="https://github.com/charliethomason/portfolio-site/blob/master/src/js/scripts.js" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">view the JavaScript I wrote here</a>.</p>
